{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"yestern-choral-mustang","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Why\n\nThe module-size soft cap (800 LOC, docs/architecture.md) has a grandfathering escape hatch: `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt` (bare-path membership) + `.github/module-size-ceilings.txt` (per-file growth ratchet), asserted in sync by tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py and enforced by a shell gate mirrored in gerrit-verify.yaml + test.yml. 12 files are currently grandfathered over the cap. The escape hatch lets over-cap modules persist and (via ceiling bumps) keep growing.\n\n## Goal\n\nDrain the allowlist to zero by splitting each grandfathered module along a real call-graph seam (never mechanically; never creating a <100-LOC file), landing each split as its own Gerrit change on main. Then remove the allowlist/ceilings escape-hatch mechanism entirely (so no module can ever be exempted again — the 800 cap becomes absolute) and add a hard gate so the module-size limit itself cannot be changed through the normal contribution process (an admin must manually override).\n\n## Decomposition\n\nPhase 1 — one child story per grandfathered module (12), each: split on a logical seam, graduate the file off BOTH allowlist + ceilings + its architecture.md remedy row, land on main.\nPhase 2 — one child story: delete the allowlist+ceilings mechanism, replace the contract test with an absolute 'nothing over 800' test, prune the architecture.md offender table, and add the limit-lock gate.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] .github/module-size-allowlist.txt no longer exists (or is empty) and no src/rebar/**/*.py file exceeds 800 LOC (verify: find src/rebar -name '*.py' | xargs wc -l | awk '$1>800')\n- [ ] The allowlist/ceilings mechanism (both files + the sync contract test + the shell gate's allowlist branch) is removed; CI still fails any new over-cap file\n- [ ] A hard gate blocks changing the 800 limit through the normal contribution process (admin manual override required); documented\n- [ ] Every child story landed on main via Gerrit (LLM-Review +1 AND Verified +1)","id":"716f-b917-9fc8-41f5","parent_id":"","priority":1,"tags":["module-size","tech-debt"],"ticket_type":"epic","title":"Drain module-size allowlist to zero, then lock the module-size limit"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784392254555896001,"uuid":"8f056bb0-322a-4d75-8b41-a324e63976b2"}